12 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Ambulance provider assessment fee. (1) Each ambulance provider
13 shall pay to the department a uniform assessment fee of 5.75% of net operating revenues.
14 (2) The AFTER THE ADMINISTRATION COSTS OF THE DEPARTMENT ARE DEDUCTED, THE department shall
15 deposit the REMAINING proceeds from collection of the assessment fee in the ambulance provider special
16 revenue account provided for in [section 14].
17
18 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Relation to other taxes and fees. The assessment fee imposed under
19 [section 2] is, in addition to any other taxes and fees, required to be paid by ambulance providers.
20
21 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Rulemaking authority. The department may adopt rules necessary to
22 administer [sections 1 through 13].
