18 NEW SECTION. Section 12. Credit for overpayment -- interest on overpayment. (1) If the
19 department determines that the amount of fees, penalty, or interest due for any year is less than the amount
20 paid, the amount of the overpayment must be credited against any fees, penalty, or interest then due from the
21 ambulance provider and the balance must be refunded to the ambulance provider or its successor through
22 reorganization, merger, or consolidation or to its shareholders on dissolution.
23 (2) Except as provided in subsection (3), interest is allowed on overpayments at the same rate as
24 is charged on unpaid taxes, as provided in 15-1-216. Interest is due from the due date of the report or from the
25 date of overpayment, whichever date is later, to the date the department approves refunding or crediting of the
26 overpayment. Interest does not accrue during a period during which the processing of a claim for refund is
27 delayed more than 30 days by reason of failure of the ambulance provider to furnish information requested by
28 the department for the purpose of verifying the amount of the overpayment.
